caption: Love this place! Perfect venue to meet up with friends during COVID. For ordering, they use the QR code where you order it on your phone and then they bring it out. We spent about 2 hours here and ordered a few rounds of drinks and the sausage platter that turned out to be more than enough food for the 4 of us. For drinks, one friend stuck to beer, and the other 3 of us experimented with various cocktails. Starting with the spiked apple cider, it was delicious and warm. You get to choose what to spike it with! Perfect for a wintery Saturday of outdoor COVID dining times. Later on we transitioned to Irish coffees, which were also tasty. The sausage platter with sides was a great dish to accompany day drinking in these bleak times. The atmosphere of this place was great for socializing. Wish we ordered the jar of mustard to remember this place. Delish wieners !

I really do hope they up their game because everything else about this place is wonderful.

Germany is notorious for making some of the best beer around. Since visiting Black Forest, I can see why! I tried a bunch. I especially enjoyed the local BK IPA. It paired great with the chicken shnitzle I dined on. The goulash though left a bit to be desired. The meat wasn't stringy - like it should be. The pasta they served with it though was delicious. Our family had brunch there on a Sunday.  The food was flavorful and unique.  We had a flatbread with cream cheese, salmon and 3 eggs on top (while my son ate it all, it was massive - could have fed 2-3 people), the German breakfast plate and then bratwurst with french fries and sauerkraut.  Honestly, we're not generally fans of German food (half my family comes from Germany and we've had a few too many culinary "issues" from eating wurst in the mountains...), but this was really good stuff.  The bratwurst with soft roll was a good expression of the genre, really well done.  the side of german potato salad had the right amount of vinegar for tang,  but maybe more mustard than I generally prefer - but still done well.  Service was slow but attentive.  The selection of german beers is terrific and unique - the Rothaus pilsener is superb and hard to find.  BTW, the place opens at 9am on Saturday and Sunday.  We had assumed that they opened so early so you could watch soccer, but alas no TVs.  There were a ton of families and kids eating breakfast/brunch, very popular.
